<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Cross1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Cross,</orth> subst. 1) the ensign of the Christian religion: <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 5.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.94" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 20</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.372" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 372</bibl>.*Used as the emblem of human suffering: <bibl n="shak. son 34.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 34, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.42.12" default="NO" valid="yes">42, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.153" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 153</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.241" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 241</bibl>.<lb />2) any thing that thwarts, vexation, hinderance, mischance: <cit><quote>I see what --es my attempt will bring,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 491" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 491</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a thousand --es keep them from thy aid,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 491" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 491</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>one silly c. wrought all my loss,</quote> <bibl n="shak. pp 257" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 257</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 2, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.136" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 136</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.4.137" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 4, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.79" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 2, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 1, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.278" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 278</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.127" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 127</bibl>.
<lb />3) money stamped with the figure of a cross: <cit><quote>--es love not him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 2, 36</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I should bear no c. if I did bear you,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.4.12" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 4, 12</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>you are too impatient to bear --es,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.253" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 253</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>